Follow your DILO and your area will stay consistent</li>\n</ul>\n',1451876156,1451876156),(563,1,5,'2016-01-06','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Asked Robbie if he is happy is the workplace as he often mopes around. Rob tells me he is happy most the time. He says the new technology, people, and customers is what he likes the most.</li>\n	<li>If you stay in touch with, and love the products we sell your job will become easier. Your passion will come through when selling and the profit and customer experience will come along with it</li>\n</ul>\n',1452029145,1452029165),(564,1,6,'2016-01-07','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Awesome month for December at 70k. Over 20k up on last year. Well done</li>\n	<li>Gain more details from customers to increase your database&nbsp;now that its quieter. This is how we keep momentum rolling through when we need it</li>\n	<li>You have a better understanding of how to accomplish our goals for BIC with your experience. Keep training the guys to help you reach your goals and incentive. I will allocate time for staff to work with you to increase their knowledge</li>\n	<li>Ensure youer AOR looks perfectly clean befor you go on days off</li>\n</ul>\n',1452119848,1452119848),(565,1,8,'2016-01-07','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Talked to Tyrone about sales and AOR being below expectation. He tells me he has a lot of things in his personal life which are making it hard for him to focus. Told him we will support him but if AOR and sales performance we will have no choice but to do a PIP. He understood and agreed</li>\n	<li>Asked Tyrone why&nbsp;when Prasad &amp; I ask&nbsp;him to do things multiple times, he still is wasting time talking to people. He tells me when he&#39;s talking to others its helping him helps take his mind off other things at home. I told him I understand, but cant accept that as an answer and we will not tolerate that anymore.</li>\n	<li>Tyrone told me he wants to improve, and his performance/baheviour has been much better today</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',1452127673,1452127673),(566,1,36,'2016-01-05','<p>Prasad</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>need to do negative every day. and I want you to action those negatives same time</li>\n	<li>returns bay must clean every day</li>\n</ul>\n',1452661086,1452661086),(567,1,17,'2016-01-24','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dont treat any sale that you dont close get&nbsp;as a failure. Bank all the information you learned from the interaction, so that you have more tools in your toolbag for the next customer</li>\n	<li>Listen to the customer. By asking open ended questions you can soak up all the answers which the customer will give you for the solution to their&nbsp;&quot;problem&quot;</li>\n</ul>\n',1453587985,1453587985),(568,1,38,'2016-01-24','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Upskill yourself in the department you are in charge of. This way you can become the go to person in this area. Let the internet be your friend by researching.</li>\n	<li>Target your weknesses. If you have no product knowledge weakness (cameras) than you will have a greater confidence going into every sale</li>\n</ul>\n',1453588146,1453588146),(569,1,44,'2016-01-24','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Aim to be the best at customer service within the CSR team. You dont have to be the fastest, or the most knowledgeble to do this. Just be your bubbly&nbsp;self and finds out what the customer wants and find their solution</li>\n	<li>Learn everything you can in retail as it will help you in your chosen career path. Retail will toughen your skin so your prepared once you decide to move on. Dealing with angry and/or upset customers will grow you</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',1453590191,1453590191),(570,1,16,'2016-01-24','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Focus on being the best overall CSR. This is your time to step-up. You have all the skills so focus on how you treat customers as we wnat to see them walk out because youve solved their issue</li>\n</ul>\n',1453604702,1453604702),(571,1,8,'2016-01-26','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Set the expectation with Tyrone this morning. Look foward to working alongside him as we have same RDO&#39;S now</li>\n	<li>Follow your DILO each and every day and your area can be the best in the store. Use your creativity for new ideas</li>\n	<li>Keep up your assertiveness with the HKR and your will earn&nbsp;respect from the team</li>\n	<li>Continue to prioritise customers. All you have to do is hit your target each&nbsp;week and do your best by the customer</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',1453753967,1453753967),(572,1,6,'2016-01-28','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>When calendar is available follow as a template and we will tweak where neccesary</li>\n	<li>Keep aiming for your target each and every week. They are aspirational targets but aim high</li>\n	<li>Learn and develop your knowledge by talking to reps.</li>\n	<li>Tell the customers what they need to know. Only over explain when customers prompt you too</li>\n</ul>\n',1453942193,1453942193),(573,1,7,'2016-01-28','<p>Starting Coaching roster next week</p>\n\n<p>Suresh Coaching time is 11.30 on a Thursday</p>\n\n<p>Askd Suresh following questions:</p>\n\n<p>Whats important for a AOR manager:</p>\n\n<p>- Stock visibility / clean / security / ticketing</p>\n\n<p>What coaching would he get the most from:</p>\n\n<p>- Best practices / what works for others / over comming objections / opportunites</p>\n\n<p>What can I do better for him as his reporting Manager:</p>\n\n<p>- going to think about this, feels he is getting good support already</p>\n',1454017513,1454017513),(574,1,48,'2016-01-28','<p>Starting Coaching roster again next week.</p>\n\n<p>Aaron coaching is 10.30 tuesdays</p>\n\n<p>Asked him what he would find most beneficial from coaching:</p>\n\n<p>- teaching / promos and setup / feedback</p>\n\n<p>How can I help him better as his reporting Manager:</p>\n\n<p>- going to think about this and get back to me on it.</p>\n',1454017642,1454017642),(575,1,42,'2016-01-28','<p>Chris Coaching 11 Thursday</p>\n\n<p>Asked Chris what is importnat in an AOR:</p>\n\n<p>- pricing / tickets / advertising / displays / clean</p>\n\n<p>Chris is now overlooking headphones as well</p>\n\n<p>Jay is Chris assistant</p>\n\n<p>Asked Chris what coaching he would get most out of:</p>\n\n<p>- feedback (good or bad) / stats and figures he loves to analyse things</p>\n\n<p>What can I do better as his reporting Manager to help him:</p>\n\n<p>- Dealing with objections and help with PK.</p>\n',1454017821,1454017821),(576,1,31,'2016-01-28','<p>Coaching on Saturday 9.15</p>\n\n<p>Asked what will he get most out of coaching:</p>\n\n<p>- Feedback and opportunities</p>\n\n<p>What can I do as a manager to help him out better:</p>\n\n<p>- going to think about this</p>\n',1454017920,1454017920),(577,1,46,'2016-01-28','<p>Jay coaching 9.30 Saturdays</p>\n\n<p>Asked what things would he get most out of coaching?</p>\n\n<p>- Feedback / opportunities / stats</p>\n\n<p>What can I do better as his reporting manager to help him achieve?</p>\n\n<p>- Catchups</p>\n',1454018113,1454018113),(578,1,12,'2016-01-26','<p>Mario coaching 9.30 Tuesday</p>\n\n<p>What is important for AOR manager?</p>\n\n<p>- Clean / pricing / stock / tickets</p>\n\n<p>What would he get most out of coaching?</p>\n\n<p>- Feedback / opportunities&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>What can I do to help him out better as his reporting manager?</p>\n\n<p>- Roleplays, small catchups on the floor</p>\n',1454018294,1454018294),(579,1,41,'2016-01-26','<p>Matt coaching at 11 on tuesdays</p>\n\n<p>What would matt get most out of coaching?</p>\n\n<p>- direction (helping with what we want to achieve)</p>\n\n<p>- feedback</p>\n\n<p>What can I do better as a manager to help him out?</p>\n\n<p>- find answers to questions or help him find answers</p>\n\n<p>- feels getting good support</p>\n',1454018463,1454018463),(580,1,38,'2016-01-26','<p>Ruwan coaching 10 Tuesdays</p>\n\n<p>What is important in an AOR?</p>\n\n<p>- clean / pricing / security / easy to find</p>\n\n<p>What would he find most helpful about coaching?</p>\n\n<p>- Feedback - good and bad / stats / opportunities</p>\n\n<p>What can I do better as a Manager to help him out?</p>\n\n<p>- getting good support / will think about this</p>\n\n<p>Ruwan was very positive about coaching and looking foward to it.</p>\n',1454018597,1454018597),(581,1,43,'2016-01-29','<p>Hannah Coaching will be 11.30 Saturdays</p>\n\n<p>Asked her questions to think about:</p>\n\n<p>What content would she get most out of coaching?</p>\n\n<p>What can I do better as her reporting manager to help her achieve?</p>\n\n<p>Will think about and get back to me on Saturday.</p>\n\n<p>Her schedule is first hour tickets - door - trolleys.</p>\n',1454020737,1454020737),(582,1,16,'2016-02-02','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Enjoying being back in CSR. More confident doing what he know&#39;s</li>\n	<li>Sammy to further train you on admin to improve your versatility,&nbsp;or cover if neccesary</li>\n	<li>Customer Service Benefits - Looks good for you. Represents the company and store well. Repeat Business. Genuinely makes people happy.</li>\n	<li>Need to offer the best service. We are not EB games or DSE where service is not the priority. Solve the customers issues, and show your enthusiasm to bring people back</li>\n</ul>\n',1454372459,1454372459),(583,1,8,'2016-02-03','<p>Jesse:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Asked Tyrone what he thinks he needs coaching on in to which he replied his attitude and emotions. Talked about how to deal with his own emotions when faced with pressure or stress. Self-awareness is important and is good to see he is understanding his opportunities.&nbsp;Experience will help Tyrone, and working with others within the team.</li>\n	<li>Talked to Tyrone about being more cooperative with his area and helping customers and what the priority and expectation is. Tyrone understands this</li>\n</ul>\n',1454470780,1454470780),(584,1,12,'2016-02-02','<p>Mario:</p>\n\n<p>Felt he had a good week. &nbsp;Had 4 customers come back on Saturday that wanted to upgrade the products that they had originally purchased.</p>\n\n<p>Black Dot for the week and VERY close to Gold Star.</p>\n\n<p>Glenn:</p>\n\n<p>Doing a great job with AOR and Sales.</p>\n\n<p>Is a very good team member and helps out alot.</p>\n\n<p>Opportunities:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tech Solutions</strong> =&nbsp;Understands this just needs to make sure not to forget to weave it into sales process.</p>\n\n<p><strong>NPS</strong> = Needs to make sure to ask customers for feedback. &nbsp;Marios customers love him and always come back to him so we need them to tell us this in the NPS.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Attention To Detail</strong> = This is to do with AOR need to focus on the details e.g. cleaning. &nbsp;Stands cabniets etc need to be clean.</p>\n',1454538519,1454538519),(585,1,38,'2016-02-02','<p>Ruwan:</p>\n\n<p>Had a very tuff week, struggled with sales and had a few issues to deal with.</p>\n\n<p>Glenn:</p>\n\n<p>Ruwan brings a great maturity to the team and is a good salesman. &nbsp;I have been very impressed with what Ruwan has bougt to the team starting full time now.</p>\n\n<p>Very good looking after AOR and keeping on top of things.</p>\n\n<p>Talked with Ruwan about keeping positive and not worrying when he dosent get all the sales that others a getting. &nbsp;He is a good enough salesman that he just needs to focus on what he is doing and the sales will come.</p>\n\n<p>Great point that Ruwan bought out was that he is adjusting on the floor and trying different approaches. &nbsp;Shows his awareness and adaptability, just need to make sure that you do not lose Ruwan.</p>\n\n<p>Opportunities:</p>\n\n<p>NPS = Ruwans customers really like dealing with him and we need them to tel us about it, dont forget to ask.</p>\n\n<p>Attention To Detail = In AOR need to focus on the small things because the big things will come along with that.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 1.6em;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n',1454538967,1454538967),(586,1,41,'2016-02-02','<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.6em;\">Pretty quiet week last week.</span></p>\n\n<p>Continual achievers:</p>\n\n<p>Prashant and Suresh</p>\n\n<p>Continual Under Achievers:</p>\n\n<p>Tyrone, Jason F, Chris</p>\n\n<p>Tory Street did a huge amount of free sessions, should contact them and see what worked well for them.</p>\n\n<p>For our percentage to sales our OL is very low. &nbsp;Need to look at why we are not achieving.</p>\n\n<p>Matt going to start auditing sales and asking team members why they didnt get OL on an invoice.</p>\n\n<p>We have lost a little bit of focus with this and need to get back on track and build it into the DNA of the team.</p>\n',1454539194,1454539194),(587,1,7,'2016-02-04','<p>Suresh:</p>\n\n<p>Did good in turnover but not in profit</p>\n\n<p>Glenn:</p>\n\n<p>Want suresh to work on being Positive.</p>\n\n<p>I asked him why he feels his sales have dropped?</p>\n\n<p>He said he is finding it hard with Lee and Jay, they are getting all the customers.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, \'Trebuchet MS\'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">Asked him if he is a good sales consultant?</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, \'Trebuchet MS\'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">He said Yes</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, \'Trebuchet MS\'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">Asked Suresh if he feels that Jay and Lee are better sales consultants them him?</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, \'Trebuchet MS\'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">He said no. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, \'Trebuchet MS\'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">Suresh has been doing some research into better selling skills and working to his strengths.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, \'Trebuchet MS\'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">I commended him for this and it shows maturity, understanding and passion.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, \'Trebuchet MS\'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">Goal for Suresh is to focus on being positive and focus on himself more and not let others get under his skin.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, \'Trebuchet MS\'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">One opportunity that I used to do was make sure to serve the first or one of the first customers of the day to get started. &nbsp;Make sure to serve every customer.</p>\n\n<p style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, \'Trebuchet MS\'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;\">Also spoke about Suresh AOR and focusing on the detail to make sure that we fix the small stuff first. &nbsp;By doing this all the big stuff will naturally fix itsself.</p>\n',1454549418,1454549418),(588,1,42,'2016-02-04','<p>Chris:</p>\n\n<p>Had a great week. &nbsp;Really liking the team work.</p>\n\n<p>Couple of observations:</p>\n\n<p>Very hard to get customers to come over from Spark because of spotify and Vodafone because of the image of Vodafone.</p>\n\n<p>We should have a database of customers that do MRO so we cna contact them in 2 years instead of 2 degrees doing it.</p>\n\n<p>Glenn:</p>\n\n<p>Chris doin a great job. &nbsp;Gave him his AOR clipboard and direction for AOR.</p>\n\n<p>Chris needs to start training team, so he is going t set up a schedule and we will go over it next week.</p>\n\n<p>Is working well with Jay and encouraging Jay.</p>\n\n<p>I reminded Chris that Jays success is his success as well because of there team work in looking after the AOR.</p>\n\n<p>Chris also needs to start taking a stronger role in representing the AOR e.g in morning meetings.&nbsp;</p>\n',1454551455,1454551455),(589,1,48,'2016-02-03','<p>Sat down with Aaron and went over the jobs that I had showen him and Hannah trough.</p>\n\n<p>Asked him how he likes the job?</p>\n\n<p>Really good, likes to keep busy.</p>\n\n<p>Doing a great job. Is a hard worker.</p>\n\n<p>Have given him his DILO/ WILO folder so he knows what to do each week.</p>\n\n<p>Also showed him the standards of how we as team need his AOR&#39;s to be. (Lock Up / Merchandise Area / Room Across From Toilets)</p>\n\n<p>Asked Aaron if he had any questions?</p>\n\n<p>Didnt have any but feels comfortable to come and ask if there is anything he dosent know.</p>\n\n<p>I am looking foward to working with Aaron in his new role.</p>\n',1454884856,1454884856),(590,1,46,'2016-02-05','<p>Prasad and I sat with Jay and discussed a couple of things with him:</p>\n\n<p>Jay doing a great job, doing really good in Connections / MRO</p>\n\n<p>Doing a great job in sales as well. &nbsp;In short time has become one of our top salesman.</p>\n\n<p>Jay still has a couple of opportunities:</p>\n\n<p>1. Needs to make 100% sure that the people he is signing up on plans know what they are signing up for.</p>\n\n<p>- we do not believe at all that he is being underhanded or dodgey, just need to make sure that the customer fully understands what they are getting.</p>\n\n<p>Jay understood this as he had a customer come back and ask him what they had signed up for even though he explained it twice to them. &nbsp;Will make sure that the customers is fully aware of what they are signing up for.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>2. &nbsp;Needs to make sure that when the alarm goes off in store that he will action it. &nbsp;Either going to the alarm going off or going to get the alarm box.</p>\n\n<p>- have noticed that Jay does not action this. &nbsp;Explained to him the importance of it and also how it is a non negtionable.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>3. &nbsp;Doing a great job in getting paid OL sessions.</p>\n\n<p>- just need to make sure that he fully communicates to Matt exacatly what the customer is wanting to do.</p>\n\n<p>- need to do thi so the complete sales to OL transition is seamless and customer gets 100% service.</p>\n',1454885458,1454885458),(591,1,13,'2016-02-02','<p>Prasad/Glenn</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>asked him about his work load. Jason always say yes when management ask him to do something</li>\n	<li>have an agreement to remove Jason as H&amp;S person and commercial person.</li>\n	<li>Jason will have nore time to do his main role (sales) and help othet staff memebrs</li>\n	<li>Jason&#39;s new AOR going to be compuetrs and Apple.&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>he need to run that place as that&#39;s his store</li>\n</ul>\n',1454891142,1454891142),(592,1,36,'2016-02-04','<p>Prasad</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Ask samanatha to create her own WILO</li>\n	<li>she is doing an awesome jb getting staff to do tasks. But Sammy need to get them to more tasks ans She can be free behind the counter</li>\n	<li>negative report need to do everyday</li>\n	<li>other tasks need to ge done weekly</li>\n	<li>if Sammy has any issues regarding admin report, she need to action that straight away</li>\n</ul>\n',1454891264,1454891264),(593,1,22,'2016-02-04','<p>Prasad</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>it is very important Philippa to reduce over 15 days repairs and do customer follo ups</li>\n	<li>need to do customer follow ups daild and nee to add notes to system.&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>everyday Philippa need to finish work at 4 and last hour do customer follow up</li>\n	<li>every Fridays make sure office is fully clean and tidy</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n',1454891401,1454891401),(594,1,12,'2016-02-09','<p>Mario:</p>\n\n<p>Had a good week, feeling everything going well.</p>\n\n<p>Glenn:</p>\n\n<p>Doing a great job is a very valued member of the team.</p>\n\n<p>Robert is going to take over his area and if he can please work with him this week to help him with PK.</p>\n\n<p>Feeback from me is that Mario has an opportunity in Connections tha