have posters in the outside and he didnt know what to put there and he couldnt find me so he moved onto another job. &nbsp;Needs to ring me or Jesse and make sure what to do. Same with promo setup needs to come and ask so WE dont slow him down.</p>\n\n<p>Also needs to make sure he does not use the side door. &nbsp;It is security and for his safety as well. &nbsp;He understands.</p>\n',1458693825,1458693825),(633,1,50,'2016-03-23','<p>Joon is happy to wear a small badge that will say that he is hearing impaired</p>\n\n<p>Joon needs to work his personal hygenie - shave, breath</p>\n\n<p>He is a professional sales consultant and needs to look like one</p>\n\n<p>Our team is of awesome team members</p>\n\n<p>are you a team member of ours?</p>\n\n<p>Yes.</p>\n\n<p>Does that make you awesome?</p>\n\n<p>Yes.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',1458695335,1458695335),(634,1,55,'2016-04-07','<p>Good Positive talk with Natasha</p>\n\n<p>Had a good week is sales</p>\n\n<p>win = processed a GE sale all by herself.</p>\n\n<p>really like how positive she is with customers and AOR</p>\n\n<p>Spoke to her about NPS and KPI sheet</p>\n\n<p>explained dots and star system - Red = Opportunity</p>\n\n<p>Reinforced the tick three boxes policy</p>\n\n<p>Needs to learn to do repairs - get help from CSR team, especially Sammy</p>\n\n<p>Opportunities</p>\n\n<p>KPI = Services, focus on providing the solution for the custpomer</p>\n\n<p>Behavioural = Slow down and focus on what she is doing</p>\n',1459993200,1459993200),(635,1,7,'2016-04-07','<p>Suresh felt he had a good week</p>\n\n<p>got a Gold Star for the week and made a good amount of profit.</p>\n\n<p>I asked Suresh about his goals and wwhat he wants to do.</p>\n\n<p>He wants to get into management.</p>\n\n<p>This is a great goal to have but he does have some opportuniteis to work on to get there.</p>\n\n<p>1. &nbsp;Livewire = Suresh will get to LiveWire definitly next year but if he pushes really hard this year he can make it. &nbsp;By making livewire he can show that he has a goal and has worked hard towards it.</p>\n\n<p>2. Behaviour = Suresh needs to work on his maturity level, &nbsp;When he completed his Ret Cert Lvl 2 his answers were intelectual and mature answers but his behaviour with the team is imature. &nbsp;I stressed to him that dosent mean you cant have fun but you need to hold yourself well and be mature to become a manager. &nbsp;Look at the example of Prasad - He still has fun but holds himself in a professional way and people can see that he is the Store Manager.</p>\n\n<p>Reminded Suresh that he is a good salesman and to believe in himself.</p>\n',1460070794,1460070794),(636,1,4,'2016-04-07','<p>Justin had a really good week last week</p>\n\n<p>He is finding it harder to sell things as he is finding that there is a lot more competition in the store.</p>\n\n<p>Justin has had 2 months off this year but is still going to make Livewire this is awesome.</p>\n\n<p>Spoke to Justin about his greatest opportunity: Services</p>\n\n<p>He said he is offering it to every customer that purchases a tv 50&quot; and above but the push back he is getting from customers is they would rather take it themselves. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Remephasized with him the way that he pitches it and to focus on more the time to setup then the idea the customer needs help to set it up. &nbsp;Same with computers with software installs and setup.</p>\n\n<p>Justin is good salesman and just needs to work on selling the complete solution (e.g. services) in his sales conversations.</p>\n',1460071054,1460071054),(637,1,36,'2016-04-05','<p>Prasad and I met with Samantha.</p>\n\n<p>Explained to Samantha that we had a shocking result on our 180 day audit and that it wasnt good enough.</p>\n\n<p>I am taking responsibilty for this as I have ownership over this and didnt take enough notice over it.</p>\n\n<p>We are setting in place new standards for the way things are going to be done in store and I have put my word on the line that we will be the best BOH team in the country.</p>\n\n<p>Great news for Sammy as well that she is being appointed 3IC in our store as is going to have specific oversight of the BOH but not be limited to that.</p>\n\n<p>Sammy has the opportunity to learn skills like Leadership and being 3IC will help this.</p>\n',1460071290,1460071290),(638,1,48,'2016-04-07','<p>Hows work being goig Arron?</p>\n\n<p>great really enjoying it.</p>\n\n<p>Aaron has been doing a great job and has been working on prioritising things so that he gets all the most important jobs completed first before everything else.</p>\n\n<p>Great feedback for Aaron from Prasad about knowing what products sell well and should be at front dumpbins. &nbsp;Encouraged Aaron to speak up if he an idea because he is definitly starting to become a retailer.</p>\n\n<p>He is found that using his clipboard is definitly helping.</p>\n\n<p>One promo setup he missed the outside posters - want him not to settle for sub standard and just to make sure that he gets the basics done.</p>\n\n<p>Aarons opportunity is that he needs to work on making sure that he completes one job before moving onto the next.</p>\n',1460072177,1460072177),(639,1,38,'2016-04-04','<p>Ruwan is getting very frustrated that he is not been able to perform as well as he believes he should in sales.</p>\n\n<p>He is struggling to get the &quot;big sales&quot; and feels he needs to get more finance now.</p>\n\n<p>I encouraged him to speak to good salespeople and get ideas off them. &nbsp;One example is Prasad he was a good sales man and he has great ideas around selling.</p>\n\n<p>Prasad encouraged him to sell all the smaller items and they will help bring his tunover up and give him profit and to serve every customer.</p>\n\n<p>Need to look at getting Ruwan to a Sales Mastery day as this would be very benificial for him.</p>\n\n<p>Ruwan is a good sales man and does well in TS OL and can do well in CS.</p>\n',1460072876,1460072876),(640,1,5,'2016-04-08','<p>Spoke to Robbie about how he feels he is going</p>\n\n<p>He is finding it tough as becuase there is more competition in store he is finding it hard to get customers as alot of the time they are already been served.</p>\n\n<p>He believes and I think is a good idea he needs to be more aware of whats going on in the store and try not to get stuck trying to serve other peoples customers</p>\n\n<p>Great feedback for Robbie on selling a computer, someone overgheard and thought he did a great job at his selling technique.</p>\n\n<p>Robbies has no problems building trust with his customers and just needs to work on converting more customers.</p>\n\n<p>He also feels that he is not selling as many big items, so going to make sure he keeps fully aware of customers in other AORs.</p>\n\n<p>Definitly getting the hang of cameras now and is starting to enjoy it.</p>\n\n<p>Robbies opportunites is to push for minimum of $25k a week</p>\n\n<p>Behavioural is to keep positive and not get down when he dosent make target an to see the next week as an opportunity to make target.</p>\n',1460073318,1460073318),(641,1,8,'2016-04-05','<p>Talked to Tyrone about making sure that he is giving out the right products for customer collection.</p>\n\n<p>Was a mix up with products on an insurance claim. &nbsp;was not entirely Tyrones fault was a mix up with Prashant.</p>\n\n<p>Great news for Tyrone he is being apointed 3IC and deserves it for all his hard work.</p>\n\n<p>Doing a great job looking after his AOR and in his new role we are sure he will do well.</p>\n\n<p>Tyrone was very happy about this and proud to go from someone who was close to been dismissed to someone who is now a 3IC.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',1460074065,1460074065),(642,1,15,'2016-04-07','<p>Hows your week gone Manali?</p>\n\n<p>She really liked this week, she really enjoyed Tuesday&nbsp;it was very scary for her but she was able to handle it and enjoyed that she was able to do it with out Sammy and Philipa and Nimita.</p>\n\n<p>Great job and it shows that she is up to the challenge.</p>\n\n<p>Talked to Manlai about the disapointing result we had in our 180 day audit for BOH and told her that it is my fault and responsiblilty but because of this result there will be cracking down and stting deadlines and specific standards for certain things.</p>\n\n<p>One of those is Cycle Count she must give the variance to Sammy by 10. &nbsp;this is a must and I will be very hot on this.</p>\n\n<p>Opportunity for Manali is to keep focused and make sure to complete CSR tasks like the AOR and overflow draw.</p>\n',1460074418,1460074418),(643,1,57,'2016-04-07','<p>Hows it going Nimita?</p>\n\n<p>Really enjoying and loving the job</p>\n\n<p>Loves the team and is finding Tyrone and Sammy really helpful</p>\n\n<p>She is finiding she is doing really well with handling customers perception when it is something that she cant help them with.</p>\n\n<p>Nimita is doing a great job and had slotted into our team really well. &nbsp;We have got her a permanet contract for 20 hours per week.</p>\n\n<p>Was happy about going from casual to permanet but was just a little disapointed that she can only get 20hours per week as she wants to work more. &nbsp;She wants to go away at the end of the year and wants to save up alot more money and dosent like just sitting around home. &nbsp;She is a person who likes to work hard and keep busy.</p>\n\n<p>Nimita was worried about her contract saying door greeter as if she goes to apply for another position or job it dosent look as good just being a Door greeter. &nbsp;I explained her contract is for a &nbsp;Customer Experience Coordinator.</p>\n',1460075249,1460075249),(644,1,6,'2016-04-08','<p>Had a catch up with Michelle to see how things are going</p>\n\n<p>She is really enjoying work. &nbsp;She is very positive about her targets</p>\n\n<p>Her target is $20k, she hasnt achieved it alot but she is getting around 10 to 15k per week which is alot more then the 3k she was getting.</p>\n\n<p>She has ownership over her area and is trying different things to drum up business.</p>\n\n<p>She really enjoyed having Adam from SSO being instore and all the cool things that he taught her.</p>\n\n<p>One opportunity she has is that she needs to get more comfcortable following up on quotes with customers.</p>\n\n<p>Also going to work alot more closely with the commercial team to make sure that she dosent miss out on those customers.</p>\n',1460075518,1460075518),(645,1,47,'2016-04-02','<p>asked rose how shes liking the job?</p>\n\n<p>she likes it and likes being part of the team.</p>\n\n<p>Talked to her about couple of things that I had to show her like credit and recharge and dealing with transfering in a cell phone that has an imei no.</p>\n\n<p>Explained that sometimes I may come across frustrated that she dosent know things but I am not and that I understand that it can be hard learning things when your not doing them all the time. &nbsp;Also explained that sometimes we dont know what to teach her untill she finds something she dosent know.</p>\n\n<p>Also on the floor I talk to her about making sure that she dosent just stand in one area and miss customers. &nbsp;She needs to keep positive and move around and serve customers and when its quiet to help ot team with there AORs or go and learn about products she dosent know about.</p>\n\n<p>She is doing a great job and we really apreciate the effort she puts into coming to the pks.</p>\n',1460075897,1460075897),(646,1,43,'2016-04-02','<p>Spoke to Hananh about how she is enjoying work?</p>\n\n<p>She really loves it and loves working with the team.</p>\n\n<p>She is a person that loves keeping busy and really enjoys when Prasad gets her in for merchandising and gives her a list of things to do.</p>\n\n<p>She also really hates standing at the front door and seeing customers needing help.</p>\n\n<p>Told her we explained the role of door greeter incorrectly and will get a better understanding of the job for her.</p>\n\n<p>Also stressed how important her role is to our team and our store.</p>\n\n<p>I have noticed the difference in her when she is helping team or customers compared to when she is on the door.</p>\n',1460076083,1460076083),(647,1,38,'2016-04-11','<p>How did your week go last week?</p>\n\n<p>Had a very slow week but had a really good Sunday.</p>\n\n<p>Marble Finance Sale and also customers friends also purchased as well because the way he explaiined it.</p>\n\n<p>This is awesome Ruwan great job. &nbsp;Sales were low but 3k profit was good.</p>\n\n<p>Spoke to Ruwan about sales and things that used to help me:</p>\n\n<p>Try to serve the first customer of the day to get a good start</p>\n\n<p>Be aware of the customers that are in the store - sometimes can get so focused on one job that you miss opportunitys.</p>\n\n<p>Ruwan won $50 from Marble finiance great benifit for just doing his job.</p>\n\n<p>Also spoke to Ruwan about Services - goal $149 per week and 2&nbsp;connections. &nbsp;Realistc goals that would encourage him to do more.</p>\n\n<p>Also spoke about Internet Leads and how easy they are and $20 spiv and opens the conversation for TS - Routers - Accesories etc etc etc.</p>\n\n<p>Ruwan very positive and encouraged.&nbsp;</p>\n',1460364409,1460364409),(648,1,48,'2016-04-11','<p>How was your week?</p>\n\n<p>Great, loving working with the team and likes keeping busy</p>\n\n<p>Asked what kind of opportunities he has (shows he is maturing)</p>\n\n<p>Aarons major opportunity is still making sure to complete one job before moving onto the next.</p>\n\n<p>Using his folder and listing jobs is a great way of doing this.</p>\n\n<p>Also spoke to him about making sure to print the promo pack and writye notes on it and to keep it in the Promo Pack folder. &nbsp;keep 5 at a time and dispose of the rest.</p>\n\n<p>Doing a great job Aaron keep up the good work. Dont settle for mediocre.</p>\n',1460364600,1460364600),(649,1,37,'2016-04-11','<p>How was your week Hon?</p>\n\n<p>Had a good week,some low sales</p>\n\n<p>Hon does a great job looking after his AOR, but has the opportunity to not get tunnel vision and miss opportunities on the floor</p>\n\n<p>Needs to try to get involved on the technology side of the store as well becuase sometimes this can be a reason for low sales.</p>\n\n<p>Hon had a great sale where he sold TS on a router:</p>\n\n<p>He said why not let us take all the hassle away for you and install it and set it up.</p>\n\n<p>Great job Hon keep up the good work. &nbsp;Set Hon a goal of doing $149 every week he is confident he can do that and we are confident he can as well.</p>\n\n<p>Major Opportunity is Connections and internet. &nbsp;speak to chriss and make sure that you are 100% ready to go on it.</p>\n',1460364979,1460364979),(650,1,22,'2016-04-11','<p>Spoke to Philipa, we had a very bad 180 day audit result for BOH.</p>\n\n<p>Alot of it was INS, Unavalible Stock and Repairs.</p>\n\n<p>We need to bring our BOH up to standard.</p>\n\n<p>I have given my word we will be 100% by end of the month and be the best BOH store.</p>\n\n<p>Philipas tasks are:</p>\n\n<p>1. &nbsp;Morning Paperwork</p>\n\n<p>2. Finances daily</p>\n\n<p>3. Repairs - must be updated at least once a week with customers and recorded on the repair. &nbsp;we will have a catch up once a week as well and go through them.</p>\n\n<p>Also we are going to train up Brenda as Admin Backup.</p>\n\n<p>Philipa agreed and will do it.</p>\n',1460486787,1460486787),(651,1,36,'2016-04-11','<p>Spoke to Sammy about getting the reports done 100% and making sure that she gets team doing what we talked about at CSR meeting</p>\n\n<p>Going to get INS report done on a monday and a Friday</p>\n\n<p>Doing IGRs daily</p>\n\n<p>Doing Unavalible Stock Twice a week Tuesdays and Thursdays,</p>\n\n<p>Admin Report on Wednesday.</p>\n\n<p>Negatives must be done daily.</p>\n\n<p>INS, Unav, Negatives must be signed off by Manager.</p>\n\n<p>Need our BOH to be 100% no exceptions. &nbsp;Do not settle for sub standard.</p>\n',1460487008,1460487008),(652,1,8,'2016-04-11','<p>Spoke to Tyrone and let him know that I will be doing his sales coaching and Prasad his leadership coaching</p>\n\n<p>Tyrone is doing an awesome Job and team speak highly of him</p>\n\n<p>But he needs to focus on sales. &nbsp;I dont need to tell him how to sell but will look for ways to help him maximise his sales.</p>\n\n<p>One specific focus of his should be NL Services / Internet and Connected Solutions.</p>\n\n<p>Tyrone finds some team members like Nimita and Hannah will come and ask him alot of questions as well as Natasha and Ruwan.</p>\n\n<p>Will talk to the team BOH questions go to Sammy, FOH questions can go to Tyrone if hes not busy.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking at changing Tyrones AOR. at the moment just need Tyrone to be more Shop Aware.</p>\n',1460487303,1460487303),(653,1,15,'2016-04-11','<p>Manali needs to make sure that she gets the cycle count variance to me by 10am</p>\n\n<p>Needs to make sure that she is scanning each product individually.</p>\n\n<p>As soon as she has given me the variance then she is to jump on CSR.</p>\n\n<p>Need to focus on the things we spoke about at our CSR meeting:</p>\n\n<p>Calls, MY NL, NPSand erecirpt.</p>\n\n<p>Manali can do a great job and I know she is capable of being great, just need to show us know.</p>\n',1460487562,1460487562),(654,1,7,'2016-04-11','<p>How was your week Suresh?</p>\n\n<p>Pretty good.</p>\n\n<p>Got a TS - Internet lead and also a Conjnection from a TV sale</p>\n\n<p>AWESOME - how did you do that?</p>\n\n<p>Asked the right questions - saw a customer looking at tv and explained about features</p>\n\n<p>showed SOny android and explained cool stuff you can do on internet like netflix then askes:</p>\n\n<p>Hows your internet? customer said slow and bad - Suresh introduced Internet</p>\n\n<p>How do you want to have the TV at home? - Wall mount - Suresh introduced TS</p>\n\n<p>Hows you Mobile phone? - Old and dumb and spend alot on it -