proud of the high standards he maintains, he does get frustrated when other staff members dont respect and look after his area though.</p>\n',1487020200,1487388770),(1038,1,43,'2017-02-18','<p>(Robert)</p>\n\n<p>Hannah is moving to Tory St branch on 3rd March and is looking forward to that, she says she has enjoyed working here and will miss the team but she felt the door greeter role was not challenging enough and did not encourage any personal growth, she also felt under valued by the other staff - that they thought of it as a &quot;lesser role&quot;. She is excited about her new role as CSR at Tory St. and believes she will get a lot more out of her new position there.</p>\n\n<p>Hannah wanted to point out before she leaves that there is a blind spot on the cameras in the audio area, and thinks we should get a camera there.</p>\n',1487377562,1487377562),(1039,1,64,'2017-02-18','<p>(Rob)</p>\n\n<p>CJ is doing well with sales and&nbsp;connections but is struggling to get accessories and warranties.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>I Talked to CJ about trying a different approach to selling addons - do not simply ask if the customer wants to take the warranty, bag etc, but instead show them the benefit - ask questions about how the product will be used and try to show the customer how the accessories will benefit them.</p>\n\n<p>This weeks focus - Accessories &amp; Supercover. - Last week 50%acc S/R &amp; 0% Wty S/R</p>\n',1487387243,1487387243),(1040,1,66,'2017-02-18','<p>(Rob)</p>\n\n<p>Jacob has done very well this week, good sales &amp; ASFM - Jacob wanted to work on his acc S/R and 2 Deg connections last week and has done oustanding with 200% acc S/R, 50% Wty S/R! (no connections but he is working on it)</p>\n\n<p>Jacob almost closed a 2 Deg connection today and is going to continue to work towards improving his connection rate over the next week.</p>\n\n<p>I have told Jacob that I am very impressed with his performance especially for a new sales person who is only working 1 - 2